post_text: Summer session is in full swing! Just a taste of the learning happening at New Dawn Charter Schools in the Humanities and Arts disciplines: Ms. Eddy's classes are working on thematic essays and contemplating the Englightenment era and its Thinkers/Philosophers, Ms. Aideyan is conferencing with students on their CAD designs in Digital Arts, while Mr. Di Paoli and Ms. Salony's classes are analyzing and interpreting Ernest Hemingway's short story "Hills Like White Elephants" for setting and literary elements. Keep up the great work everyone! Next up: Math and Sciences. #summerscholars #newdawncharterschools

post_text: Last week, Executive Director at New Dawn Charter Schools, Dr. Sara Asmussen and Rivka Miller had the distinct pleasure and honor to be invited to meet with NY 1 News Anchor and Author, Cheryl Wills at the NY News 1 offices in Chelsea. We met with a panel of other New York based non-profit organizations and Cheryl Wills sharing our stories and learning how to increase media awareness for the work that we do throughout the five boroughs. Thank you to Cheryl Wills, Sara Asmussen, and Jane Brody at #VicusPartners for this informative afternoon. #nonprofit #newdawncharterschools #ny1
